<item>
            <title>[LU-997] port the fix of &apos;max nested link count&apos; from upstream e2fsprogs to master-lustre branch</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-997</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;commit 08ae93a2eda03817deabf08d4da9015a283ed56b&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Niu Yawei &amp;lt;niu@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   Sat Nov 19 23:08:03 2011 -0500&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    libext2fs: enforce a max nested link count in ext2fs_find_block_device()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Define EXT2FS_MAX_NESTED_LINKS as 8, and check the link count to make&lt;br/&gt;
    sure we don&apos;t exceed it in ext2fs_find_block_device() and&lt;br/&gt;
    follow_link().  This fixes a potential infinite loop in&lt;br/&gt;
    ext2fs_find_block_device() if there are symbolic loop links in the&lt;br/&gt;
    device directory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Signed-off-by: Niu Yawei &amp;lt;niu@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    Signed-off-by: Theodore Ts&apos;o &amp;lt;tytso@mit.edu&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
